desc:MCP Ambisonic Format Converter
//
// Bundled with the ReaperMCP extension (Batch S1). A zero-dependency ambisonic normalization /
// format converter for an ACN-ordered HOA bus. JSFX ships with REAPER, so this needs no third-party
// plug-in (unlike the IEM/SPARTA/ambiX suites the spatial orchestration tools drive).
//
// Driven by spatial.convert_format, which discovers the "Conversion" slider by name and sets its mode:
//   0  SN3D -> N3D     per-ACN gain  g(l) = sqrt(2l+1)              (ANY order)
//   1  N3D  -> SN3D    per-ACN gain  g(l) = 1/sqrt(2l+1)           (ANY order)
//   2  ambiX (ACN/SN3D) -> FuMa      first-order / B-format ONLY   (reorder + W*1/sqrt2)
//   3  FuMa -> ambiX (ACN/SN3D)      first-order / B-format ONLY   (reorder + W*sqrt2)
//
// Why FOA-only for FuMa: FuMa (Furse-Malham max-N) is a legacy convention with a single universally
// agreed table only at first order (classic B-format: W X Y Z, W scaled by 1/sqrt2). Above first order
// there is no single agreed FuMa max-N set, so the tool refuses HOA FuMa rather than ship a subtly
// wrong matrix — HOA interchange should use SN3D/N3D. Modes 0/1 are exact for any order.
//
// Channel model: ACN index k has degree l = floor(sqrt(k)) and order m = k - l*l - l (m in [-l, +l]).
// ACN first-order layout is W(0) Y(1) Z(2) X(3); FuMa first-order layout is W X Y Z.

slider1:mode=0<0,3,1{SN3D to N3D,N3D to SN3D,ambiX to FuMa (FOA),FuMa to ambiX (FOA)}>Conversion

